This paper deals with the problem of enforcing Lipschitz constraints on convolutional neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with training neural networks and improving their performance. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as convolutional neural networks are widely used in computer vision tasks. The third likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with designing and training neural networks. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with improving the robustness of neural networks. The fifth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper deals with designing a new parameterization for convolutional operations.
